---
import "../styles/hero.css";
---

<!-- Suggested meta title: Technology & Product Consultant for Non-Technical Founders -->
<!-- Suggested meta description: I help non-technical founders and companies design, build, and automate software that saves time, reduces costs, and drives business impact. -->

<section id="home" class="hero" aria-label="Hero">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero__container">
    <div class="hero__top">
      <header class="hero__intro">
        <p class="hero__eyebrow">Technology &amp; Product Consultant</p>
        <p class="hero__role">For non-technical founders and companies.</p>
        <h1 class="hero__title">
          I help non-technical founders and companies design and automate software
          that solves real problems.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero__subtitle">
          We reduce technical uncertainty, avoid cost overruns, and build
          solutions that impact the business&mdash;not just the code.
        </p>
        <p class="hero__value">
          I help non-technical founders and companies save time and money by
          designing, building, and automating software that solves real problems.
        </p>
        <p class="hero__keyword">
          As a technology product consultant and technology consultant, I serve
          as a digital product consultant focused on practical process
          automation and business outcomes.
        </p>
        <div class="hero__actions" role="group" aria-label="Primary actions">
          <a class="hero__btn hero__btn--primary" href="/services#how-i-work">
            See how I work
          </a>
          <a class="hero__btn hero__btn--secondary" href="/content">
            Read my insights
          </a>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="hero__visual" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="hero__visual-card">
          <svg
            class="hero__graphic"
            viewBox="0 0 360 360"
            role="presentation"
            aria-hidden="true"
            focusable="false"
          >
            <defs>
              <linearGradient id="hero-gradient" x1="0" y1="0" x2="1" y2="1">
                <stop offset="0%" stop-color="var(--hero-primary)" />
                <stop offset="100%" stop-color="var(--hero-accent)" />
              </linearGradient>
            </defs>
            <rect
              x="22"
              y="22"
              width="316"
              height="316"
              rx="46"
              fill="none"
              stroke="var(--hero-border)"
              stroke-width="2"
            />
            <circle cx="122" cy="122" r="52" fill="url(#hero-gradient)" />
            <circle
              cx="240"
              cy="220"
              r="70"
              fill="none"
              stroke="var(--hero-accent)"
              stroke-width="3"
              opacity="0.5"
            />
            <path
              d="M74 235 C130 195, 180 185, 250 215 S320 280, 300 312"
              fill="none"
              stroke="var(--hero-primary)"
              stroke-width="3"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              opacity="0.65"
            />
            <circle cx="256" cy="118" r="11" fill="var(--hero-accent)" />
            <circle cx="96" cy="252" r="10" fill="var(--hero-primary)" />
          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hero__container hero__body">
    <!-- PROBLEM -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__problem" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
      <h2 id="problem-title">
        The problem isn't technology. It's making bad technical decisions.
      </h2>
      <p class="hero__lead">
        Most teams struggle because they build before they're clear. The result:
        wasted budgets, slow progress, and decisions that don't move the
        business forward.
      </p>
      <ul class="hero__list" aria-label="Common pain points">
        <li>Expensive software that goes unused</li>
        <li>Automations that don't save time</li>
        <li>Total dependency on technical profiles</li>
        <li>Endless projects with no clear return</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__who" aria-labelledby="who-title">
      <h2 id="who-title">
        I work with people who need clarity, not technical jargon.
      </h2>
      <ul class="hero__list">
        <li>
          Non-technical founders who need to make technology decisions with
          confidence
        </li>
        <li>
          Companies looking to automate processes and reduce operating costs
        </li>
        <li>Teams that need to validate an idea before investing in development</li>
        <li>
          Businesses seeking pragmatic solutions, not unnecessary complexity
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW I HELP -->
    <section
      class="hero__section hero__how"
      id="how-i-work"
      aria-labelledby="how-title"
    >
      <h2 id="how-title">A product mindset, not a tools mindset.</h2>
      <ol class="hero__steps">
        <li class="hero__card">
          <span class="hero__step-number">1</span>
          <h3>Diagnosis</h3>
          <p>I understand the real business problem and its constraints.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hero__card">
          <span class="hero__step-number">2</span>
          <h3>Solution design</h3>
          <p>I define what to build, what not to build, and why.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hero__card">
          <span class="hero__step-number">3</span>
          <h3>Automation &amp; development</h3>
          <p>I implement practical solutions focused on impact.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="hero__card">
          <span class="hero__step-number">4</span>
          <h3>Iteration &amp; improvement</h3>
          <p>I refine based on real usage and results.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <a class="hero__link" href="/services">View services</a>
    </section>

    <!-- EXPECTED RESULTS -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__results" aria-labelledby="results-title">
      <h2 id="results-title">Results you can expect</h2>
      <ul class="hero__list hero__list--checks">
        <li>Time savings</li>
        <li>Cost reduction</li>
        <li>Clarity for decision-making</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- TRUST SIGNAL -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__trust" aria-label="Trust signal">
      <p>
        I work with discretion and a strong focus on impact; references can be
        shared upon request.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- AUTHORITY -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__authority" aria-labelledby="authority-title">
      <h2 id="authority-title">
        I think and write about technology applied to business.
      </h2>
      <ul class="hero__topics" aria-label="Topics">
        <li>AI applied to business</li>
        <li>Process automation</li>
        <li>Product vs features</li>
        <li>Real mistakes and hard decisions</li>
        <li>Build in public</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="hero__category-links" aria-label="Content categories">
        <a href="/content/ai-business">AI applied to business</a>
        <a href="/content/automation">Process automation</a>
        <a href="/content/product">Product vs features</a>
      </div>
      <a class="hero__btn hero__btn--secondary" href="/content">
        Explore content
      </a>
    </section>

    <!-- FINAL CTA -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__final" aria-labelledby="final-title">
      <h2 id="final-title">
        Do you have a technical problem and don't know where to start?
      </h2>
      <p>Let's talk before building anything.</p>
      <a class="hero__btn hero__btn--primary" href="/contact">Contact</a>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="hero__section hero__faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
      <h2 id="faq-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="hero__accordion">
        <details>
          <summary>What does a technology product consultant do?</summary>
          <p>
            I help non-technical teams make confident product decisions, reduce
            risk, and focus on outcomes before building anything.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>How does process automation save time and money?</summary>
          <p>
            By removing repetitive manual work, process automation frees teams
            to focus on higher-value tasks and reduces operational overhead.
          </p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>When should I involve a digital product consultant?</summary>
          <p>
            If you're unsure what to build, need clarity on scope, or want to
            avoid costly rework, that's the right time to bring in a digital
            product consultant.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</section>
